# Plugin Platform v2 (current architecture)

This repo now uses a broad, capability-gated plugin model. Do not assume legacy resource-only plugins.

## Key facts

- Plugin SDK surfaces include: `resource`, `api`, `media`, `seo`, `jobs`, `adminUi`.
- Manifest entries declare `trustMode` and `capabilities` in `apps/api/plugins.manifest.json`.
- Loader enforces capability checks before plugin surface registration.
- Runtime dispatch is centralized via `apps/api/src/plugins/plugin-runtime.ts`.

## Agent rules for plugin-related changes

- When adding plugin behavior, update both SDK contracts and manifest validation if needed.
- Keep examples in `apps/api/plugins.manifest.example.json` aligned with schema.
- If UI/runtime plugin state changes, update `apps/admin/app/plugins/page.tsx` and API plugin service payloads together.
- Prefer sandbox-friendly defaults: minimal capabilities, explicit declarations.
